questions.scenario:
You are debugging a production issue where a `PaymentService` in a Spring Boot application is failing to roll back database changes. The code looks like this: 

java
@Service
public class PaymentService {
    public void process(Order order) {
        // ... validation logic
        saveOrder(order);
    }

    @Transactional
    public void saveOrder(Order order) {
        repository.save(order);
        throw new RuntimeException("Simulated Failure");
    }
}


Even though `saveOrder` is marked `@Transactional`, the record is persisted in the database after the exception is thrown.
